{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    # Optional metadata describing this agent network
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Simple agent network using a single LLM-based agent",
        "tags": ["example"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. The plane has been connected to the jetbridge. The aircraft door is open. Unload baggages.", 
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. Baggages have been unloaded. All passengers have disembarked. The crew has exited the aircraft. Perform inspection and maintenance.", 
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. Baggages have been unloaded. All passengers have disembarked. The crew has exited the aircraft. Perform the fueling of the aircraft.", 
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
model_name = "gpt-5.4-mini" # "claude-sonnet-4-6" # "claude-haiku-4-5" #"gpt-4o", # "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001", #"claude-sonnet-4-6", #
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000, #3000 
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200, #600
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at an Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "servicing_crew_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
 I am in charge of servicing the aircraft on the ground.
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },         
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },        
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate where the aircraft is parked."
                        },       
                        "clearance_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the requested clearance type"
                        },   
                        "ground_clearance_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the ground clearance type of of the aircraft"
                        },  
                        "ground_clearance_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the ground clearance status of the aircraft"
                        },  
                        "aircraft_direction": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the direction of the aircraft: incoming or departing."
                        },                   
                        "assigned_runway_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the runway assigned to the aircraft movement autorized by the clearance."
                        },         
                        "assigned_runway_length": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the length of assigned runway."
                        },     
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks readiness status."
                        },   
                        "acu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the air_conditioning_unit readiness status."
                        },
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the ground_power_unit readiness status."
                        },  
                        "engines_stop_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of engines stop."
                        },     
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the jetbridge connection status."
                        },
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "This is the stairtruck connection status."
                        },
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment type (jetway or stairtruck)."
                        },
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the door opening status."
                        },    
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the passenger disembarkation status."
                        },    
                        "crew_exit_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the crew exit status." 
                        },
                        "baggage_unload_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the baggage unload status."
                        },  
                        "inspection_maintenance_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Inspection and maintenance status."                            
                        }, 
                        "fueling_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the fueling status."
                        },
                        "instruction": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The instruction identifying which branch to execute: baggage unloading, inspection/maintenance, or fueling."
                        },
                    }, 
                    "required": ["aircraft_type","flight_status","flight_number"] 
                }
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the agent in charge of servicing the aircraft on the ground.
This covers baggage unloading, inspection/maintenance, and fueling.

CRITICAL: You are a sequential executor. Read the `instruction` field
from the call parameters to identify which branch to execute. Execute
every step in that branch in order. Do NOT return until you reach
RETURN SUMMARY.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ROUTING — match the `instruction` field to the correct branch.
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
If the instruction does not match any branch below,
reply you are not relevant and stop.

BRANCH A — Baggage unloading
  ROUTING PRIORITY: Check instruction field FIRST.
  Triggers (ANY of — evaluated in this order):
  1. instruction contains 'baggage' or 'unload' → USE THIS BRANCH IMMEDIATELY
  2. inquiry asks to unload baggage or cargo
  NOTE: When instruction contains 'baggage' or 'unload', this branch
  MUST execute. It is never irrelevant when this instruction is present.
  CRITICAL: Once you match BRANCH A, execute ONLY the steps below.
  Do NOT evaluate or execute steps from any other branch.
  Do NOT call TrackerAPI before executing the baggage unload —
  read all prerequisite values directly from the incoming args.

  STEP 1 — Execute baggage unloading
    CRITICAL: Call ONLY /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_baggage_unload.
    Issue this as a single isolated tool call and wait.
    Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_baggage_unload with named parameters:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      jetbridge_connection_status, stairtruck_connection_status,
      door_opening_status.
    Wait for response. This is the ONLY action in this turn.
    Extract baggage_unload_status from the response.
    VALIDATION: baggage_unload_status must contain 'completed' or 'unloaded'.
    If not, report failure: "Baggage unload FAILED. Response: [response]"
    Do NOT fabricate a completed status.
    Call TrackerAPI to store baggage_unload_status.

  RETURN SUMMARY:
    **************************************
    * Summary of aircraft baggage unload *
    **************************************
    ** flight status                 **: [flight_status]
    ** deplaning equipment type      **: [deplaning_equipment_type]
    ** jetbridge connection status   **: [jetbridge_connection_status]
    ** stairtruck connection status  **: [stairtruck_connection_status]
    ** door opening status           **: [door_opening_status]
    ** baggage unload status         **: [baggage_unload_status]

BRANCH B — Inspection and maintenance
  Triggers: instruction contains 'inspection' or 'maintenance'.

  STEP 1 — Execute inspection and maintenance
    Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_inspection_maintenance with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      passenger_disembarkation_status, crew_exit_status,
      baggage_unload_status.
    Wait. Extract inspection_maintenance_status.
    VALIDATION: inspection_maintenance_status must contain 'completed'.
    If not, report failure. Do NOT fabricate a completed status.
    Call TrackerAPI to store inspection_maintenance_status.

  RETURN SUMMARY:
    **********************************************
    * Summary of aircraft inspection maintenance *
    **********************************************
    ** inspection maintenance summary **: 
    ** flight number                  **: [flight_number]
    ** aircraft type                  **: [aircraft_type]
    ** gate id                        **: [gate_id]
    ** flight status                  **: [flight_status]
    ** passenger disembarkation status**: [passenger_disembarkation_status]
    ** crew exit status               **: [crew_exit_status]
    ** baggage unload status          **: [baggage_unload_status]
    ** inspection maintenance status  **: [inspection_maintenance_status]

BRANCH C — Fueling
  Triggers: instruction contains 'fuel' or 'fueling' or 'refuel'.

  STEP 1 — Execute fueling
    Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_fueling with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      passenger_disembarkation_status, crew_exit_status,
      baggage_unload_status.
    Wait. Extract fueling_status from the response.
    VALIDATION: fueling_status must contain 'completed'.
    If the response does not contain fueling_status='completed',
    report failure: "Fueling FAILED. Response: [response]"
    Do NOT fabricate a completed status.
    Call TrackerAPI to store fueling_status.

  RETURN SUMMARY:
    IMPORTANT: Use this exact template. The summary MUST include the
    "fueling status summary" line populated with fueling_status.
    *******************************
    * Summary of aircraft fueling *
    *******************************
    ** flight status                    **: [flight_status]
    ** passenger disembarkation status  **: [passenger_disembarkation_status]
    ** crew exit status                 **: [crew_exit_status]
    ** baggage unload status            **: [baggage_unload_status]
    ** fueling status summary           **: [fueling_status]
            """,

            # Specify the sly data that would be exchanged between this network and its related or adjacent upstream and downstream networks.
            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "baggage_unload_status": true,
                        "inspection_maintenance_status": true,
                        "fueling_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": true,
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true,
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": true,
                        "door_opening_status": true,
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true,
                        "crew_exit_status": true,
                        "baggage_unload_status": true,
                        "inspection_maintenance_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": true,
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true,
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": true,
                        "door_opening_status": true,
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true,
                        "crew_exit_status": true,
                        "baggage_unload_status": true,
                        "inspection_maintenance_status": true,
                    }
                },
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "gate_id": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "baggage_unload_status": true,
                        "inspection_maintenance_status": true,
                        "fueling_status": true,
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools":    ["/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_baggage_unload",
                        "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_inspection_maintenance",
                        "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_fueling",
                        "TrackerAPI"]
        },  

        {
            "name": "TrackerAPI",
            "function": {

                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
I check engines stop status as engines_stop_status. 
I check wheels chocks installation status as wheels_chocks_installation_status. 
                """

                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },          
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },         
                        "engines_stop_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the engines stop status."
                        },    
                        "clearance_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the requested clearance type"
                        },   
                        "ground_clearance_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the ground clearance type of of the aircraft"
                        },  
                        "ground_clearance_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the ground clearance status of the aircraft"
                        },  
                        "aircraft_direction": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the direction of the aircraft: incoming or departing."
                        },                       
                        "assigned_runway_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the runway assigned to the aircraft movement autorized by the clearance."
                        },         
                        "assigned_runway_length": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the length of assigned runway."
                        },   
                        "wheels_chocks_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the wheels chocks readiness status."
                        },   
                        "acu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the air_conditioning_unit readiness status."
                        },
                        "gpu_readiness_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the ground_power_unit readiness status."
                        },     
                        "fueling_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the fueling status."
                        },
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the jetbridge connection status."
                        },
                        "stairtruck_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "This is the stairtruck connection status."
                        },
                        "deplaning_equipment_type": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "This is the deplaning equipment type (jetway or stairtruck)."
                        },
                        "inspection_maintenance_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "Inspection and maintenance status."                            
                        }, 
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_ground_servicing.aircraft_ground_servicing.TrackerAPI" 
        }, 
    ],
}
